tracks.title: Sean Tyas - Quarantine Megamix - Volume 2
tracks.description:
As a thank you for the truly amazing support thus far on the new remix of Christina Novelli's "It'll End in Tears", here is Volume 2 of the Quarantine Megamix Series.  This time it's a 100% Producer Set with some tracks dating back over 12 years :)

tracklist is up to you, but I'll try to check the comments if you have any IDs, as many were bootlegs.

Here is a direct link to the It'll end in Tears remix: http://bit.ly/tearstyas

Enjoy!

tracks.title: Orla Feeney - Time Out (Tytanium Preview)
tracks.description:
Coming on 24 November 2014

Also known as the sultry "voice" of Tytanium Sessions, Orla Feeney steps up to flex her muscle on her new production, Time Out. 

Going down the tough tech trance route with heavy spoonfuls of psy rolled into a nice filling mixture that oozes with character & punch. 

Get down with this.

tracks.title: Madwave - Perceptions (SoundCloud Preview)
tracks.description: Coming to Beatport on 10th of November 2014

tracks.title: Standerwick & Brian Flinn - Vanaheim (Tytanium Soundcloud Preview)
tracks.description:
Release Date: 13th October 2014

Definitely needing no introduction for either of these powerhouse producers, Ian Standerwick & Brian Flinn, load up, don their viking suit raiding gear, eat their broccoli & spinach, and set out to display power of godly order. 

All the drive and push you would come to expect from these two teamed up, and then some! 

Highly resonant acid lines form the blades of this one, dipping quickly into a breakdown, before it gets a second wind of pure fury. 

Oh yes.

tracks.description:
VII014: Freedom Fighters - Clockwork (Sean Tyas Remix)

Out now: po.st/VII014

Sean Tyas takes Clockwork - the spooky, 2016 minimal Psy Halloween release from Freedom Fighters and gives it the C4 treatment. Absolute hammers from the mane of the moment Tyas whose production has entered a whole new chapter of awesome.

tracks.title: John Askew - Shine (Sean Tyas Remix)
tracks.description:
Out now on WAO138 >> po.st/shineremix

Remixing one of the first tunes to ever hit the Who Afraid Of 138?! imprint, Sean Tyas makes his mark on one of John Askew's finest works. Once again putting his famed energetic touches to the test, the renowned trance producer matched the high standard of production quality we've grown accustomed to. It's high powered trance music at its finest, stuffed with huge amounts of replay value. Time to 'Shine'!

Sean Tyas meets long time good buddy Greg Downey to explore both sides of where they are at musically... simultaneously.

Let there now be light because it is only always darkest before dawn...

VII043: Sean Tyas - In Bloom
Beatport release: 22.07.19

Editorial:
Who on earth would have the capacity and skills to successfully fuse psychedelic trance with 80s electro vibes? Who would be brave enough to try? Who is the man who consistently pushes the boundaries and refuses to play by the rules? Who is the shepherd leading the sheep? Press play and youll have your answer. Big respect. We adore this record and cant wait to hear what direction the audio chameleon that is Sean Tyas goes in next.

tracks.title: Sean Tyas & Niko Zografos - Drop Two (Preview)
tracks.description:
It all started in the basic concept of a remix of one of Sean Tyas dancefloor bangers from 2007. Sean Tyas and Niko Zografos originally just intended to bring this monster up the the level of 2019 standards, but it took on its own character throughout the whole production process.  Cybernetic enhancements and genetic upgrades have led to an entirely new being connected to the original yet completely standalone in its own right, leading us to not call it a remix at all but an auditory sequel, if you will.

Meticulously (and we mean that, as this final version is actually the 63rd master) crafting the original vibe using old and new tools spread over 3 different machines and 2 DAWs, we bring you Drop Two, to experience this vibe today, 12 years after the original Drop was created.

Coming July 8th
